* Cold black eyes watched Prowl as he fell backwards and landed hard on his 
rear, seeing him express his pain as his damage becomes more noticable then 
ever.
But all she did was watch, simply see him.
She followed his movements as he jumped to his feet, her logic relieved that 
he was at least alright now...sort of.

But even as she watched, she knew that this was wrong and that she shouldn't 
have hurt him. A ting if guilt in her spark.
She faught her beast modes to attach him again, wanting to rip him apart. 
But this time she resisted, using as much will power as she could handle.

As she heard Prowl ask a question she understood she began to shift her 
weight uneasily, her systems far to ferel to communicate to him, but 
systematic and logical enough to know what he was talking about.

Of course she wasn't all right! And she wanted to scream that at him, but 
she didn't know how to form the sounds into the peoper words.
Her systems were overloading from too much power, her adrnalin was through 
the roof, she was trapped in this mode and didn't know how to get out.
She wanted...no...NEEDED help, but she didn't know how to ask for it.

As the mode shifted she began to look towards Prowl nervously, almost like a 
dog that knew it did something bad and was now facing its owner.
But she began to slightly mew as well, pathetic little sounds that 
communicated her uneasyness.

She wanted help, and this was the best way she knew how to ask for it.
But at any moment she could become vilent again, and she wanted help to keep 
those mood swings under control. But also to keep her beast modes under 
controle as well.

The mode soon began to pace the room, almost seeming to want a way out like 
she wanted a way out of this terror which was true.
But the pacing was also doing something else as well, it was keeping her 
beast modes under control...for now.*
